<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd">
<en-note><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px;">Installing PHP</span></div><div> </div><div><br/></div><div>We will be installing the version 7.1</div><div>=&gt; sudo portsnap fetch</div><div>=&gt; cd /usr/ports/lang/php71</div><div>=&gt; sudo make install clean</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px;">Installing the PHP Extensions</span></div><div><br/></div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">cd </span>/usr/ports/lang/php71-extensions  </div><div><span style="color: rgb(169, 169, 169);"># Enable the OpenLDAP support ( you might need to use for phpLdapAdmin)</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> sudo make install</span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px;">Installing the PHP module for Apache</span></div><div><br/></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> cd </span>/usr/ports/www/mod_php71</div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">sudo make install clean</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> cd</span> /usr/local/etc</div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">sudo cp</span> /usr/local/php.ini-production /usr/local/php.ini</div><div><br/></div><div># Edit the php.ini file and set the Timezone for your City</div><div># Timezone Link: <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/timezones.php">http://php.net/manual/en/timezones.php</a></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">date.timezone</span> = America/Toronto</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px;">Enable the PHP Support in the Apache Server (httpd.conf)</span></div><div><br/></div><div># Make sure that the PHP module is enabled in “/usr/local/etc/apache24/httpd.conf&quot;:</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">LoadModule </span>php7_module        libexec/apache24/<a href="http://libphp5.so">libphp7.so</a></div><div><br/></div><div># Add index.php after index.html (means if index.html not found use index.php)</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;IfModule </span>dir_module<span style="font-weight: bold;">&gt;</span></div><div>    <span style="font-weight: bold;">DirectoryIndex </span>index.html index.php</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;/IfModule&gt;</span></div><div><br/></div><div># Add after the last line: Include etc/apache24/Includes/*.conf</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">AddHandler</span> application/x-httpd-php    .php </div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">AddHandler</span> application/x-httpd-php-source    .phps </div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Testing the PHP Module</span># Lets create a PHP file inside the DocumentRoot (<a href="http://www.karshi.ca">www.karshi.ca</a>)</div><div># We will call it php_info.php and insert the following code:</div><div>&lt;?php <span style="font-weight: bold;">phpinfo()</span>; ?&gt;</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div># We can visit <a href="http://www.karshi.ca/test.php">http://www.karshi.ca/test.php</a></div><div># You should see a lot of info there</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">PHPpgAdmin ( PostGRE)</span></div><div><br/></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> cd</span> </div><div><span>/usr/ports/databases/phppgadmin</span> &amp;&amp;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> sudo</span> <span>make install</span><br/><span>Note: Don't make 'clean' it will delete the work directory where the &quot;conf&quot; folder is. </span></div><div><br/></div><div>Create the </div><div><span>phppgadmin.conf</span></div><div> file (or you can add these lines in the Apache https.conf):</div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">sudo vim </span></div><div><span>/usr/local/etc/apache24/Includes/</span><span>phppgadmin.conf</span></div><div><br/></div><div>----------------------------------------------------------</div><div><span>Alias</span> <span>/phppgadmin </span>&quot;<span>/usr/local/www/phpPgAdmin</span></div><div>&quot;</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;Directory</span> &quot;</div><div><span>/usr/local/www/phpPgAdmin/</span>&quot;<span style="font-weight: bold;">&gt;</span><span>Options</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">None</span><span>AllowOverride </span><span style="font-weight: bold;">Limit</span><span>Require </span><span style="font-weight: bold;"> ip</span> <span>10.10.10.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;/Directory&gt;</span></div><div> -------------------</div><div><br/></div><div>Edit &quot;</div><div><span>/usr/local/www/phpPgAdmin/conf/</span><span>config.inc.php</span></div><div>&quot;</div><div>Near Line 88:</div><div>change this  ---&gt;  <span style="font-weight: bold;"> $conf['extra_login_security'] = </span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">true</span></div><div>;</div><div>To  this        ---&gt;   <span style="font-weight: bold;">$conf['extra_login_security'] = </span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">false</span></div><div>;</div><div><br/></div><div> </div><div><br/></div></en-note>
